This command will configure the Docker credential helper for your account.

It will create a new script named docker-credential-scw. 
This script will be called each time Docker needs the credentials and will return the correct credentials.
It avoid running docker login commands.

USAGE:
  scw registry setup-docker-helper [arg=value ...]

ARGS:
  [helper-directory]   Directory in which the Docker helper will be installed

FLAGS:
  -h, --help   help for setup-docker-helper

GLOBAL FLAGS:
  -D, --debug            Enable debug mode
  -o, --output string    Output format: json or human
  -p, --profile string   The config profile to use
